<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Sphere Drake seeks Dollars 150m via New
York offering
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SPHERE DRAKE, the insurance and reinsurance company, is to raise more than
Dollars 150m (Pounds 100m) through an initial public offering in New York,
channelling most of the cash into its London market and Bermudian insurance
subsidiaries.
The move reflects increasing confidence among investors in the commercial
insurance and reinsurance markets where rates have risen sharply in recent
months. Sphere Drake, whose majority shareholders include Electra Investment
Trust, Dai Tokyo Fire and Marine, and Center Capital Investors, is a leader
in the London reinsurance market. Net assets of the group's London-based
insurance company currently amount to Pounds 75m. Net premium income
amounted to Pounds 200m in 1992.
The IPO offer will be underwritten by a group of underwriters for whom Smith
Barney, Harris Upham, Lazard Freres and Salomon Brothers are acting as
representatives. The IPO is scheduled for the middle of September, although
no decision on timing has been made.
</TEXT>
