FT  05 JUL 93 / Major to be pressed for July by-election
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP STEPHENS, Political Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE GOVERNMENT will this week come under strong pressure to set July 29 as
the date for the Christchurch by-election.
The Liberal Democrats have indicated that they are ready to break with
tradition and seek to move the by-election writ in the Commons themselves if
Mr John Major seeks to delay the poll until September.
Mr Major has delayed the by-election because of the potentially devastating
impact on party morale if the Conservatives' 23,000 majority is overturned.
But the government may well pre-empt the Liberal Democrats because MPs are
expected to break for their long summer recess before July 29.
The prime minister is also being advised by colleagues that a defeat in
September would further sour the mood at the Conservatives' autumn
conference in Blackpool, increasing the pressure on his own position.
