FT  03 JUL 93 / Finance and the Family: House prices rise by 1.6%, says
Nationwide - At a Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
House prices rose by 1.6 per cent in June, the fourth consecutive monthly
increase and the biggest since May 1991, according to figures from the
Nationwide building society. The Nationwide house price index has now risen
3.5 per cent since the start of the year, but prices are still down 3.5 per
cent from June last year. The average house in the UK now costs Pounds
53,710.
Brian Davis, Nationwide's operations director, said: 'A recovery in the
housing market does appear to be underway, but it is still fragile with
turnover still only slightly above last year's depressed levels.'
