with only minor investment activity.' The group's service business
activities, then comprising the European fire protection division and the
American office cleaning and maintenance division which was sold at the
start of June, continued to make 'substantial' profits despite the
recessions in both the UK and the US.
An extraordinary charge of Pounds 16.1m resulted from the sale of National
Cleaning.
