FT  03 JUL 93 / Tougher law on porn video traders
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A PRIVATE member's bill designed to facilitate prosecutions against traders
in pornographic video recordings completed its passage through the Commons
yesterday.
The video recordings bill, already approved by the Lords, provides for the
strengthening of the certification system operated by the British board of
film classification.
The freedom and responsibility of the press bill, and the right to know
bill, were among more than 50 measures which failed to reach the statute
book on the final day allocated to private members' legislation.
