preferred to pull back and to return in the next days,' said an Italian
military spokesman.
Meanwhile the Italian cabinet agreed to send almost 2,500 servicemen to
Somalia at the request of the United Nations and the US and a further 1,200
troops to support UN humanitarian operations in Mozambique, writes Robert
Graham in Rome.
In Bonn, Germany's parliament approved deployment of 1,700 troops to
Somalia, limited to providing logistical support for other UN peacekeepers.
The vote cleared the final hurdle for Germany's biggest deployment of ground
forces abroad since the second world war.
